  This evaluation is the result of both experimental and          7731 1451
theoretical input, as explained below. It contains the (n,gamma), 7731 1451
(n,n')m, (n,2n) and (n,3n) cross sections for reactions on Ir-193.7731 1451
                                                                  7731 1451
The Ir-193(n,n')Ir-193m isomer cross section was determined by    7731 1451
combining both theoretical and experimental information. The      7731 1451
GEANIE gamma-rays detector at LANSCE, Los Alamos, was used to     7731 1451
measure the excitation function for this isomer from threshold    7731 1451
up to ~30 MeV [Ne02]. The GEANIE team (Nelson, Fotiadis, Devlin)  7731 1451
measured very well four (4) gamma-lines feeding the isomer at the 7731 1451
g-rays energies of 219.2, 389.1, 398.8, and 483.2 keV. This data  7731 1451
provides only a partial measure of the total feeding of the isomer7731 1451
and theoretical calculations are needed to infer the total isomer 7731 1451
production cross section by taking into account unmeasured gamma- 7731 1451
lines and direct feeding of the isomer. The GNASH nuclear reaction7731 1451
code was used to this end. Latest available information on the    7731 1451
levels scheme was used in these calculations. For details on the  7731 1451
choice of the optical model, continuum level density prescription,7731 1451
and gamma-ray strength function description, see [Ch99].          7731 1451
                                                                  7731 1451
The level scheme used in the GNASH calculations was adjusted to   7731 1451
better reproduce the 4 observed gamma-lines excitation functions, 7731 1451
in particular for the two highest-spin states feeding the isomer. 7731 1451
The calculated ratio of (n,n')m_tot / (n,n')m_4gammas was then    7731 1451
used to correct the GEANIE data for the missing contributions.    7731 1451
The inferred cross section for the isomer population is what is   7731 1451
included in MF=10,MT=4, i.e. including all the gamma-cascade      7731 1451
feeding.                                                          7731 1451
                                                                  7731 1451
The (n,2n) and (n,3n) cross sections were also calculated with the7731 1451
GNASH code. The (n,2n)g+m1 and (n,2n)m2 [9+,241 yr] were          7731 1451
separated out and are included in two subsections of MF=10,MT=16. 7731 1451
The (n,3n)g and (n,3n)m1 [11/2-, 4.9s] are given separately. The  7731 1451
(n,3n)m1 can be added to the (n,2n)m2 in the disappearance        7731 1451
channel.                                                          7731 1451
